76561198004537895,Recommended,268400,15710331,"Posted: 6 May, 2015",all,Rommel,"Jawoll, Generalfeldmarschall!Accessibility: 9/10Replayability: 8/10Graphics: 6/10Sound: 8/10Panzer Corps is an accessible wargamer in the tradition of Panzer General. As the name suggests, it is a Korps-level wargamer that focus on maneuver and combined arms tactics. It eschews complex supply lines and routes in favor of easy to understand icons and actions. Playing a grand campaign from the cobbled stones of Poland in 1939 to the plains of Ukraine in 1943 and back to ruined Berlin in 1945 is gratifying in the sense that you get a sense of ownership in the accomplishment of your units. They will earn their Ritterkreuz, and so will you too if you last that long.Multiplayer is good, not exceptional. Be prepared for a long evening if you so chose to play.A serious quibble in this otherwise impeccable game is the DLC's which seem to pester and tease gamers with content. The DLC's are quite enjoyable in its own right but not worth the asking price. Get the core game, it is worth it. Get the DLC's when they are on sale."
76561198186497274,Recommended,268400,32151034,Posted: 3 June,all,DanielHall15,"While I do not agree with the ridiculous pricing for this game (140 bucks total with all DLC!?), the game itself is a pleasant throwback to a time when games lived on actual strategy and tactics rather than shiny bling, The old Panzer General has been both well-preserved and has received some welcome updates, first and foremost the separation of moving and attacking, which preserves a lot of sanity.The AI is actually capable of defending itself most of the time, even if in many cases strongpoints invariably consist of AA and artillery next to each other, infantry in urban terrain, and a river to cover the flank.Buying the entire collection (which comes about half of the normal total in the complete bundle edition when on sale, which is when I bought it, because the 140 bucks are just nuts) provides a huge selection of battles in addition to the rich unit pool - after 30 hours I am not only still on my first campaign, but I haven't even made it to Barbarossa yet."
