,Recommended,268400,28265399,"Posted: 8 December, 2016",all,overman,"After looking for a good TBS game in the WW2 genre and being overwhelmed by the choices available, I chose to stick to something tried and true. I played PG 3d and 'Scorched earth' years ago and wanted something not too simplistic but not requiring a college text to learn. I found the perfect balance in Panzer Corps, a game I have been unashamedly addicted to since the beginning of the year.For older gamers like myself that prefer turn-based games that have strategic/tactical depth and an immersive experience, PC is a near-perfect fit. I've slogged my way through the stock campaign as well as 90% of the DLC available. I've spent almost 1k hours loving this game and I haven't even touched the modding community's offerings yet!For people with an above average understanding of WW2 history, armies, equipment, and tactics this game is a pleasant dream come true. However, some of my complaints are the lack of simple features:a- Animations could be improved to show tank treads moving, truck wheels turning, soldiers marching, etc. 2D terrain appears dated, could use simple enhancements like trees swaying in the wind, water moving, waves on beaches splashing.b- There could be more differentiation between tactical styles for different armies (I've found that using the same style of play works the same for Germans, Soviets, or Americans),c- Units on high ground (hills, mountains, forts) should have stronger attack/defense benefits,d- Comprehensive GC includes many what-if scenarios....but WHY isn't the Pacific war ever included in the official DLC?? I mean c'mon, its not that hard to model the USMC/USN taking on the Japanese across islands, the Phillipines, Okinawa, and a what-if invasion of mainland Japan. The UK's defense of Burma and India, China, etc...all ignored!!!e- modding could be a little more easier / user-friendlyOverall, and excellent addiction that fans of WW2 TBS will enjoy;  just be sure to have lots of time available!"
