76561198095684897,Recommended,268400,30726404,Posted: 25 March,all,Simon Lancaster [ANWF],"Took a little while for me to get into this but once I played more of the tutorial battles I started to like this game more and more. At first, it seems quite slow and cumbersome. The graphics aren't great and moving pixelated squares around may not seem exciting. However, once you play the 5th tutorial battle you are right in the middle of a full-on battle and trying desperately to counter the AI. The difficulty level is quite high and single player is a challenge. Your army gets stretched as you go across the map and you have to make quick decisions on where to reinforce, and how many units to move where. On a tactical level this game is very good.Battles move along quickly with fast fighting, and it is very easy to load up a game in your campaign and play a game or two after work. There is not much strategic planning as there is no base building, no allocating resources over wide areas, and no planning on a grand map. All the strategic decisions are made as you play your battles with units carrying over into your next battle, and new units being made available before each battle.It is quite a simple design but the battle mechanics are very good, and with even the early battles being a challenge it really keeps you engaged. The campaign DLCs add a lot of content as well. Recommended for wargamers, and especially so in the frequent Steam sales. 8.5/10"
