76561197962946527,Recommended,268400,21433387,"Posted: 24 February, 2016",all,SDC Robert Locksley,"I can only begin by suggesting that this is ""Panzer General in HD"". There are many (mostly visual) improvements and as many additional complications, but the game remains fundamentally the same-a somewhat simplified tactical wargame worthy of many classic board war games (thanks to TTG, WRG, SSI and their pioneering predecessors) and the original PG itself, born of those little cheap boxed map-and-counter games those of us old or keen enough to remember started with. I would recommend the basic game at the start-veterans may miss the irritating arbitrariness of the original (weather and supply reducing the game to a perfect and deeply aggravating historic re-enactment are still optional, thank goodness!), but I believe as a veteran tabletop wargamer of thirty years that you will still find the challenge inherent in the original game, but with some shiny extra features that may please you. I must add that I am currently ploughing through the original game, crrently on sale (24 Feb 2016) and as such I must also add that DLC is also available. However I have chosen to avoid the DLC for now until I am familiar with the main game, in order to ensure that I know what I am letting myself in for. Feel free to do as you like, but as an ""old sweat"" familiar with long drawn-out military campaigns fought from the safety of my own four walls, this will do and saves me hours of setting up a table and putting it all away afterwards."
