76561197974248323,Recommended,268400,32280927,Posted: 8 June,all,Pwnface Killington,"A very solid war game that has a myriad of addons. The base game has you controlling German Panzer forces through a series of scenarios that cover the war. If you complete them within a certain turn limit then the campaign branches into some ""What if"" scenarios.  I personally found the turn crunch my least favorite part of the game.The unit scale seems to be maybe company level, but its not entirely clear. The distances of each hex is once again unclear.Which is fine, the game abstracts a lot and that keeps it simple, the game maybe falling a little short of being a ""hard core"" wargame. But at the same time its pacing is nice, and the tactical thinker is rewarded.I've gotten the most mileage out of the ""Allied Corp"" expansion though I do look forward to trying Soviet Corp when the time is right. Allied Corp, the AI is fairly scripted which makes save scumming the generals greatest weapon. The RNG is a wee bit to wild at times, and you will watch inexpilicable things happen like motorcycle troops beating tanks in open desert.On sale this game is a total steal, and to be perfectly honest if you enjoy turn based wargames this price is worth it at full price."
